The project developed electricity monitor prototypes. The latest is capable of measuring up 30 circuits simultaneously and is designed to be located next to distribution panel or consumer unit. The cost per circuit monitored is then dominated by the cost of the current transformer (e.g. &amp;pound;15) required to measure current on a circuit rather than the measurement processing storage and communication.







